column2: Cold day- rain on and off- sunny when I checked the secchi
Temp 35- ice along shore- cloudy day.
No bloom yet!  Best we have seen it in 5 years.
Clear blue sky- 90 degrees- mild algal bloom.  3 chicks in the osprey nest on the platform- clearest lake has been in 5 years during June.  Rain gauge: 2.5 inches from 6/14 to 6/21.
Heavy rains this week- high wind during one storm.  Rain gauge: 3 inches from 7/14 to 7/21.
Very dry conditions but lake level is stable- beautiful day- fewer blooms this year.
This past week- 10 inches of rain.  Heavy silt from intermittent streams- loose bog in the lake.
Algae is gone!  Lake looks great after the frost and big rains.
Beautiful day- good fishing- warm weather.  Osprey chicks are growing.
Bright- shiny day.  Frequent daily rain.
Frequent rains- much more weed growth.
Cloudy day and a large algae bloom noticeable on the shore- heavy rains this week.
4" rain this past week- high- muggy.
Sunny- warm fall day - seagulls present - recent algal bloom.
Best July reading ever recorded for Desair- (secchi and temp)
Cloudy- first algae bloom on 8/2 for the season.
Algae bloom started 8/1/96- sunny windy and cool.
Windy. Brown algae. Low lake level.
Osprey left their nest due to lake freeze out and 90% fish loss.
Beautiful day.  No herons or osprey on lake due to severe fish loss - winter kill.  No spawning beds this spring.  Rain gauge reading 1 inch from 5/1/97 to 6/8/97.
Warm- windy.  Started to rain.  Very dry conditions.  Rain gauge reading from 6/1/97 to 6/24/97=0.3 inches.
Algal bloom thickest of the year.
Heavy rains.  Deepest algal bloom of the summer 9-4 through 9-16.
Algae bloom all month.  Cloudy and very windy today.
Ice off 4/3/98.  No osprey or herons.
Very little rain this month or last.
Very early spring- first algae bloom.
6 inches of rain last week.  Increased sediment.
Why is the lake brown this year
Breezy and hazy.  Geese have left.
Sunny- a pair of geese have nested 55 feet up on the osprey platform.
Fished with my sons.  4 goslings survived the 55' fall and are swimming with their parents.
Clear blue sky- light breeze- saw an eagle- blue + green heron.
3.5 inches rain in past week.  Calm breeze.  Niece Jenny helped with collection.
Windy- sunny- son Brent helped with collection.
Low grade green algae bloom all month.  Minimal rain.
Osprey pair on nest- first time in four years.  They arrived on 4/22.
Windy- a dry spring- and heavy frost on 5/18.
Calm- partly cloudy- and two pairs of geese with half grown goslings.
Sunny- breezy- and thick algae scum pilling up on shoreline.
Dave Blumer here to collect with us- also nieces Anna and Josey.  Osprey doing well.  Color strip #6.
4.25" rain on the 8th- lake level up two feet for a few days- and much sediment.
Two osprey chicks spotted and two geese families have grown and flown to big lakes.
Sunny- continued excess algae- and frequent rains.
Hazy day- thick algae- and over 8" of rain for the month.
Sunny- continued algae blooms- worst summer since 1992.
Colorstrip #3- beautiful fall colors- hazy sun- and breezy.
Sunny- breezy- leaves 80% fallen- and no rain in three weeks.
Sunny- 70 degrees- warm- and leaves all naked.
Sunny- heavy spring rains- and excess slit in April.
Sunny- four pairs of geese raising families and placed goose fence along cabin.
Record June rains- 4" of rain this past week- and O2 dead zone at 13 feet.
Heavy rains all month with excessive erosion.
Dry for three weeks- 4" of rain this past week- quiet lake- and lilly pads in bloom.
5" of rain on August 1 with major erosion and wash outs.
Scum of blue green algae on lake surface.
Clear and sunny- low oxygen- and turned aerators early.
2 inches of rain- 18 goslings- more fisherman than usual.
Sunny- swim with Kate and Anna
3.5 inches of rain- worst algae bloom- hot and humid.
Talked to ice fishermen who reported- "crappies 7-9"

column1: good job with the aerator- keep it going!"

column2: April 1st ice 15" thick- aerator running yet O2

column1: are low. Ice off lake on April 15th. Aerator started Dec 17th 2002 and
turned off April 14th 2003 (4 months). Aerator keep lake from a fish

column2: Sunny day- warm- fishing with my 90 year old mother.
First major algae bloom of the summer. Sunny day-

column1: six boats out on lake - fishing.

column2: Fresh beautiful summer day- 5 boats out on our small lake- fishing.
Perfect day- on pontoon with Brooke Lee- three year
Brooke helping Grandpa on the pontoon- she stayed in tent overnight with Grandma. Carol helped me collect data.
Sunny- beautiful fall colors- Joyce Abel with me.  Brent helped me collect data.
Full sun- woods white with spring flower bloom
Partly cloudy- windy.  Best Secchi reading since 1991.  Dams are in.
First wonderful day of June.  Had frequent rains.
Bright sun- 50 F.  3 days after 9" rain- lake up 3 feet.  Brown silt.  Major bloom.
clouded up and rained as I started study- loon called- osprey called while eating in tree
full bloom- 20 dead fish every 100' of north shore - stinks
less than .5 inch rain in the last 2 months- one week in 90's- drought- thermocline at 12'
7.5 inches of rain the week before- restored lake to normal levels- minimal outflow
7 inches rain in august- 2 domestic geese- white - take up residence on the lake- canadian geese gone- 6 boats on lake
sunny day- domestic geese are found to belong to the Coveys
200geese on lake- full fall colors- sunny cool day
Clearest the lake has ever been. Hazy sunny day- birds singing in a light breeze.
Lake is very low- two fishermen.
Blue green algae in clumps. Two fishermen. Rained an inch this past week. Weakened tree turning color- a small maple.
Dought has lake level down a foot. No water in outlet. Full sun day.
Algae bloom after 4 inches of rain. Lake still low. Trees are in full color. Lake has been popular to fish.
Windy- partly cloudy- out with Carol- saw Louie the Loon
Calm clear day- no boats on the lake
Breezy- temp in the 80's- all is well

It has been a sad summer for rain. We have had enough to keep the grass green but no heavy rains since mid June. All of the creeks leading to Desair are bearly flowing. ponds are nearly dry. Lake down two feet from normal. No outflow at all.
introducing Bill McClain- lake home owner- to the water testing project.

column1: Beautiful day- lost my cellphone into the water pulling up the anchor!##@!!

column2: Turning cloudy- floating algae- no boats as winter kill in March. Less than an inch of rain in past 30 days- very dry.
Clear day- no boats- last year 5-8 boats daily.
Clear day- no boats- last year 5-8 boats daily.
Marge Lisi here to see how this is done. Sunny day- no boats.
Lake Association party: "Meet in the Middle" gathering of boats and pontoons for pot luck and fun
Study with granddaughters' Brooke and Brynn. Clear day.
Sunny- no boats- drought all summer
Study with Carol- blue sky with puffy clouds- awesome tree clolors.
With Marge Lisi Hazy day- calm- leaves budding. Two otter playing
Marge and Gerry collecting. Sunny- Mallard hen with ten ducklings. children playing on shoreline
Sunny and calm. Had lunch on the lake. found posters in the wall of cabin from WWII. They were cool!
One of the best Secchi readings ever since I started recording in 1993
Sunny- very muggy and a storm is coming.
Partly cloudy- no one else on lake- one loon
Sunny and calm. Good rains this month. finished interior of cabin with native wood from our land.
Breezy- pPicnic with Cate- Cathy- Marilyn and Joe- Partly cloudy- warm. 5.3" rain in June

column1: Very best Secchi reading since beginning records in 1993

column2: Secchi with my grandgirls and their frinds as they tubed behind the pontoon
Out pontooning with Brooke and Brynn- sunny warm day
Sunnyafter a storm. We had Meet in the Middle party where all Lake Assoc boaters tie up together for snacks and visiting. Great fun. Had a total of 8.3' rain this month. Our six year drought is over!
Sunny- calm and humid. I saw a flowing clam and wondered if a sea glue may have dropped it  Lots of rain thiis week
Sixty degrees- feels good! We are working on the streambank restoration
Sunny after 0.2' of rain. For the first time this summer an algae bloom is occuring.
Sunny warm day. Carol and i stayed at the cabin over night enjoying every minute together.
Sunny and breezy- boater out catch crappie. Desair Lake Kinship Fishing Derby was held on the twelth with nine kids and six boats for a wonderful afternoon.
small areas of blue green algae
Gerry Lisi with me on paddle boat after my surgery
Breezy- temp of 77 degrees. Thick algae bloom- worst ever in May.

column1: Beautiful day- toured lakeand our daughter in law's new house
Three loons on the lake- Jeff says there is a nest. We did not find it. May have flooded out.

column2: Nicole and Maddy Hodkiewicz joined me

column1: Clear blue sky - Maddy filmed the procedure.
Nicole and I talked about design for the Henkel detention pond

column2: Took Jeff on the pontoon to do DNR lake core samples
Drought- we had to water our newly built rain garden

column1: Gobs of blue green algae. I have been seeing more of this every year this past 5 years

column2: Bright beautiful day- very dry- lake down 18 inches.
Bright and colorful day as the trees change to their fall decor.
Clear skies- brown water. Went for a walk and pontoon ride with my wife- Carol; her birthday
Clear sunny day- water brown from heavy rains. a perfect day to be on the water.
Early algae bloom- lots of rain- high clouds. Beautiful songs from the birds in the woods.
Beautiful day. Deep algae bloom. I am on the lake with Bill James- UW Stout doing a separate lake study.
I'm out on the lake with my dog- Chip. Partly cloudy- rained 7 inch in August. Calm and humid at 72 degrees today.
High clouds- lake very green- one other boat on the lake- over 7 inches of rain in August!
Warm day with the worst algae bloom I've seen in years!. The smell of algae is causing irritation.

column1: Trees are turning color and the woods are lovely.

column2: Benton and Nisa staying at the cabin

column1: Loon family with two chicks spotted

column2: Sunny- lovely day. Carol joined me on the pontoon.
Sunny and breezy. Took Lamer visitors on pontoon tour of Desair Breezy pleasant day
Pontooning with Granddaughter- Brynn- taught her how to take a reading
Carol and our dog Chip with us on pontoon

column1: Only one adult with the two chicks that are nearly adult size
Warm with a Blue Green Algae bloom
Beaver dam has raised water level
high rains add to the murkiness of lake
Beaver Dam and excess rains keep lake levels high
Our looms laid eggs but we never saw hatchlings
Loom pair spent the summer on Desair

column2: Sunny and calm- temp in 70s. three loons- lots of birds singing- one other boat.
Sunny and beautiful- enjoyed touring in the pontoon
Sunny and breezy. Mother loon sitting on next along north shore. Algae bloom just starting
Sunny and 76 degrees. loon family calling
Mostly sunny 82 degrees with fluffy clouds. Saw only one loon
Pontoon tour; cool but nice- loon on nest- Blue flag blooming- flock of cedar waxwings.
Partly sunny; Good report on Total P from DNR
Hot + muggy; next day rained 3.5 inches.
Water silty after heavy rains; hot- humid- sunny morning.
Pontooning on lovely morning - loon family with 2 chicks
Pontoon ride - lost one chick to eagles
Sunny; lots of fishermen on lake.
Toured lake right after a rain - high sediment.
More of a brownish/green algae.  No scum on the lake this year.
Partly cloudy; pontooned after tour of Natural Conservancy.
Cool Wind; Chick is growing and with only one parent.
